<DOC><DOCNO> AP880902-0264 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-02-88 1803EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f AM-XeroxSoftware     09-02 0163</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Xerox Software,0169</SECOND><HEAD>Xerox To Announce New Desktop Publishing Software</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Xerox Corp. is scheduled to release on Tuesday anew generation of its Ventura Publisher personal computer software,the best-selling software for desktop publishing in the IBM PCmarket.   The new software will be easier to use and more flexible and isthe first of its kind that allows several computer users who areconnected in a network to work on the same document, Xerox saidFriday.   Dataquest Inc. estimated that Ventura Publisher had a 62 percentshare last year of the market for desktop publishing onInternational Business Machines Corp.'s personal computers andcompatible machines. Dataquest estimates the desktop publishingmarket will grow to $5.3 billion by 1990.   The suggested retail price of the core product, VenturaPublisher 2.0, is $895. A package including networking software hasa suggested retail price is $1,295. The products are developed by aXerox subsidiary, Ventura Software Inc. of Salinas, Calif.</TEXT></DOC>